caption: Best somosa in dmv
Flavors of India is a magical place.
the chicken tikka masala rocks my universe 🤟💗
I always arrive purchasing some food in this place. I like the fast customer service and well made dishes. Great work.
Their lunch buffet has really good vegan options
All the reviews are not real the last time i was there i saw a lizard in the resurant walking on the floor

This is the best Indian food I have ever had. The veggie vindaloo was flavorful, spicy, and an excellent portion. The tamarind sauce was outstanding with the samosas and roti. I will definitely be ordering from here from now on. They also have clearly marked vegan options on the menu. I loved everything I ordered.
Worst malai kofta I've ever had. The gravy was thin and it was all flavorless. Samosas and garlic naan were good.
Delicious authentic Indian food and great service
Long wait. food was ok
The best

Let me start with saying I adore the taste of the food and options. I’ve ordered food to go here 10+ times. A little pricey but very good and fresh. However in the last month I’ve had two orders of food have plastic cooked into the food. I told them the first time when I found two pieces (about the size of dimes)in some naan. Now I’ve found some again inside a samosa and I felt the need to write a review since obviously this is an issue. I’m tempted never to purchase again which is a bummer since I probably eat their food at least few times a month.
Got take out and the food was 3 out of 5 stars not worth the price at all. But they gave me a whole lot of rice
The food was good but the environment was lacking. Inside the restaurant, it was very dull, several tiles in the ceiling were stained and need to be replaced. This experience left much to be desired.

Ordered an order of paneer makhani and an hour later I received a container with about 3 cups of sauce and only 3 pieces of the small paneer cubes in it. To say I’m upset is a huge understatement. For $26 I should have had enough for at least a full meal rather than only 3 bites.

Above average Indian food. Been there quite a few times - around 10. Reasonably priced and the food tastes good overall. What I don't like about them is at least on two occasions I was charged a 18% service charge, in addition the credit card receipt has a section for tips and if you don't pay attention you end up paying the tip twice.
During weekday, no items at all.

My wife, kids and I are visiting from Wisconsin. We ordered carryout (Lamb Korma, Chicken Korma and Butter Chicken...plus Peshwari Naan and Rice Pudding). The food was done on time and was delicious...we ate it all. The people at the restaurant were also very nice.
Ordered biryani and mutter paneer. Both dishes didn't taste like they were freshly made. Won't visit again.
Lamb Rogan Josh was excellent, heat was exactly to order. Garlic Naan and rice pudding excellent as well. Maybe throw a fork in when delivering to a hotel?

If u want to have the worst food that a starving man will not eat. You can go to this place. Last time the waiters had a fight in the resteraunt and were punching each other. This place is horrible do not go at any cost.
Food, atmosphere, and service was great!
A simple order of 2 naan, 1 curry and 1 soup took 50 minutes. Taste was like any other average indian restaurant. Not worth the wait
Great place!  Good food and good prices.

Never ever order food from here even for your worst enemy. Wish I had read the negative reviews before placing the order.  Food was inedible and was not even close to the description of the dishes. Restaurant was not receptive of the feedback we immediately provided.  1. Paneer makhni - was made of watery soup with boiled paneer. 2. Malai kofta - tasted almost like yogurt 3. Complimentry plain rice was soggy 4. Naan was average

I chose one star because that’s the lowest rating I can give to this restaurant. I never wrote any bad reviews till now in my life but this one I am compelled to the reason is bad food and if that’s not enough then the worst response from the restaurant person. The food was horrible. We ordered paneer makhni and it was like paneer dipped in tomato soup. Gravy was thin like soup and tasted like tomato soup. Malai kofta was like pakoda kadhi another terror. We immediately called the restaurant person informing about the food and the arrogant person replied to us that this is how we cook and that’s how it is made. Not even a single word of apology. Now we are scared that hopefully none of us fall sick because of this food. I read Some reviews here that people fell sick after eating in this restaurant. If you really love Indian food and don’t want to have nightmares please avoid this restaurant. I am never eating here in my life.
One of the worst place to go. The Dal was stale I am sure how can they server stale food. Paneer dish was made canned tomato soup.
Terrible service. The staff was so arrogant. Food didn’t have any flavor in it. Wasn’t worth the 30 minutes we spent waiting to be given simple food. Flavorless flavors of India!
Food was okay. The waiter wasn't to friendly or happy .

Lunch Buffet by Chance at this Hole in the Wall place.  Man.  Fantastic..  Two words.  GOING BACK.  However, I did notice that out of 5 tables, my table was the only one that didn't get served NAAN.  But, with everything else being so delicious and fantastic, I didn't care but I let the waiter know.  It was kind of cold and it looked like it is run down, but I just might have found my new goto Indian Buffet fix place.  Awesome!
Good food, bhindi masala was nice and spicy
Food is fresh and served quickly without having you to wait for long. Excellent staff service!
They serve authentic Indian dishes which are great in taste!!!
I love their appetizers and dips. What a great place to chill with your buddies on Friday nights! 5 stars to Flavors of India.

If you’re in the West End, this is a tiny hidden gem that’s not on the overrated Zagat list. Best East Indian cuisine in the D.C. area. Tradition is forefront...these folks know how to bring the heat! Plus, sizable portions and wonderful customer service. Family-owned. Now that Meiwah has closed it’s doors, there’s not many familiar, well-loved haunts left. But this one is still here...enjoy!

I have been in US for 5 years now. This is the worst restaurant that I have been to in every possible way and that made me to write my first review. I am sure that the food served in this restaurant is prepared at least 2 days before. Above all the service is the too bad.

We ordered biryani, puri, chana masala, naan, veg and non veg curries. It was the worst biryani we ever had. Not at all fresh. Naan was dried up as if it was prepared a day before. Dough used for puri was not fresh, puri had a sour taste. Chala masala seemed to be prepared on the same day but taste was below average. On top of this staff was rude.

If the rating had ZERO I would have given that! Such a tasteless n rotten food served. We did order reshmi kabab, palak chat, tomato soup n panir tikka, everything is horrible. I’m not somebody who will leave negative feedback but I had to write this review while I’m trying to eat! Don’t waste your money n mood by visiting!!
Bad food ever tasted!!!!!
It's the worst restaurant I've ever been. Food is the worst and it doesn't seem like fresh.
Their dessert section is nothing less than paradise. Although kheer is my favorite, but I also liked their gulab jamun and kulfi that makes the meal wholesome.
The place is awesome when it comes to customer service .. we had kids with us and they are bound to be naughty but the restaurant were patient enough and provide good customer service..
Tried out their happy hours once and it was worth it. Their specialty cocktails, artisan beers and creative small plates all are excellent.

We ordered for Chicken chole and enjoyed it thoroughly. The place is apt for spending good time with your family and friends. The chicken was cooked perfectly and the scent of the spicy flavors tasted delicious.

Went out for a movie on last weekend and later dropped by this place for grabbing a lunch. The food was good and quantity was adequate. We ordered for Aloo-Tikka chaat and navratna korma for my sister asshe is a pure vegetarian. The food was delightful and service was great.

The food is amazing and staffs are nice and friendly! Our waiter shook our hands after dinner and refilled our rice plate before we could even ask. Such a nice, cozy place to sit down for some great Indian food. We had the chicken tikka masala and cheese naan and it was definitely some of the best I've had.

This restaurant serves excellent Indian food for affordable prices. Their chicken dhaniya is very tasty and will leave you begging for more. The serving size is large, so there's likely enough for some late-night bites. The garlic naan is large and delicious as well. The wait staff is friendly and attentive. This is a gem of a place. The ambiance isn't glamorous or awe-inspiring, though looking past those unimportant aspects I rate this five stars for the quality, price, and size of food as well as promptness and courteousness of the servers.

I sincerely appreciate their wait service. My second time was tonight & both times my fried & I arrived close to closing. No issue. Treated us like we arrived at opening I got butter chicken & my friend ordered lamb chops. Food was awesome. Will be back again.

Every dish I've tasted from this restaurant has been great. Each bite is complex and holds a plethora of flavors. I especially recommend the palak paneer and the baingan bharta. Basmati rice (included with the meal) and naan complement the curries quite nicely, but honestly the curries can also easily be eaten alone; they're just that good. Order a cup of cardamom chai to complete your tastebuds' blissful journey through this restaurant's menu

First time I was very skeptical walking by because there was no one inside. Sat down with immediate service from the host. We ordered the curry lamb, shrimp kurai (waiter suggested us), and puni bread. All were great! Our food came out fairly prompt...partly because we were the only diners. I will definitely be back for the food and for the great service. Our server Islam was awesome! He was very attentive and ensured that we had everything we needed....our glasses never went empty.

Flavors of India is my go-to spot for Indian food in the Washington DC. It's a comfortable atmosphere and the servers are friendly and happy to give you recommendations. The menu is extensive and everything I've tried has been flavorful and fresh, not too oily like at other places. Quantity of food is just right for me to share or take home leftovers. Prices are on lower side. Overall a place that never disappoints.

The food was fresh and they know how to add spice without overpowering the vegetables. The way they made saag was unique. I have been to a LOT of Indian restaurants in DC, NY and Philly and most places make it with a thick and heavy cheese base. Here, it is not drenched in sauce and you can taste the fresh vegetables. “Flavors of India” is my favorite Indian restaurant in the city. I always get it delivered, so I can't speak to the atmosphere. The food itself is great.

Hi Flavors of India! I just want to thank you for the lovely lunch I had yesterday. What I enjoyed most of all is that the food is delicious and the portions are generous, yet the price is not as high as in other places

It was authentic indian test. We were on vacation for few days and we wanted to eat something spicy n testy like indian test. We were very happy to go at this place. Don't change ur mind to see the furniture or the crockery. Bcz it was not like fancy. Bt yes the food was too good. Specially spicy paneer makhni and wheat flour paratha and dal tadka. We suggest for indian people, you can go blindly at this place to feel our test. Staff people are so kind bt slow service.
Worst restaurant ever I visited, We have ordered Garlic naan and onion kulcha they were too hard to eat, paneer curry has little salt pepper and water nothing else.. never recommended
Super nice owners and wait staff.  Not crowded.  Very convenient location.  Solid food, can't beat their masala!

Flavors of India is incredibly good for its food, vibe and service. We had keema, house special bhuna, and lamb korma. It's especially great and comforting to sit in this homey quiet restaurant after a tough long day for me. We had Rasmalai for dessert too. It had exotic flavor, but didn't impress us too much. In general I would just say dining here was the best thing I've done today. I wasn't a big fan of Indian food but this place earned me.

We have ordered delivery from flavors of India many times but yesterday was the first time that I've dined in--I have to say, the food quality is very good and taste was delicious. I've eaten at other Indian restaurants in DC but they were often overpriced but not so tasty comparing the price. I highly recommend eating here if you want high quality Indian food at a reasonable price. In comparison to Indian restaurants in Los Angeles and New York, Flavors of India is still high on my list. It also helps that the staff was very friendly and expedient in their service. I will undoubtedly be ordering from here/dining in again very soon. Best of luck Flavors of India. Good going.

I always order a mango beef samosa, lassi, garlic naan, and chicken tikka masala--all of course were quite flavorful and not excessively oily. I've eaten at other Indian restaurants in DC but they were often overpriced and not as tasty. I highly recommend eating here if you want high quality Indian food at a reasonable price. In comparison to Indian restaurants in Los Angeles and New York, Flavors of India is still high on my list. It also helps that the staff was very friendly and expedient in their service. I will undoubtedly be ordering from here/dining in again very soon.

I love almost all the dishes I've tried in Flavors of India. The spices and the flavors are rightly balanced to remind one of what a good made Indian meal must be like. I love the feel of the place, the hindi tunes that float around and the hospitality of the owner, the host there! Very strongly recommend this place. My personal favorites are spinach chat, chicken korma, madras chicken and paneer saag !

There food was delicious. Service was wonderful. The roti is always hot and fresh. I love this restaurant because they have a wide range of options for food and beverages that's affordable. My friend is vegan and I'm halfway between vegetarian and vegan but it's is so much to choose from. We have been twice and have had a great experience. I really don't know why they don’t have more branches especially since they are so close to Georgetown. And they have an upstairs bar that's open til 1AM on a weekday!?! Hands down the best Indian food I've had being in DC for 5 years.

Here's why I like to give this restaurant 5 stars. Come and talk to the people who run this place, and meet the waiters that work here.  At first they'll be reserved, but I can guarantee you, they'll treat you well. I've lived here for 6 years in Foggy Bottom, it's fast simple and good.  People who come here and rate it low, I assume are expecting a Michelin star dining experience, this place is not that. It's a place with good food, that's convenient and it'll give you a cozy space to talk to friends.  You want that? Come here.

This is one of the best restaurants in Washington. Walking in we were greeted by warmth- warm smiles and warm hellos from the owner and a cozy setting. He seated us and tended to our needs throughout all of dinner and was the absolute embodiment of the compassion and love inherent in Indian culture. The vegetable samosas were outstanding and the tika masala and naan was perfect.  The flavor of India is an authentic and excellent experience of Indian food and hospitality.

This place was very beautiful.  First, the substance: The food was very tasty. I ordered the chicken tikka masala, and they gladly accommodated my request to make it extra spicy. My group also ordered the chicken vindaloo, and the beef seek kabob -- both tasted great.  Second, the service: The servers were incredibly friendly and helpful. They answered all of our questions (i.e. What is this sauce? Can we make the dishes extra spicy? Etc.) They also gave us some food items and dessert on the house. And, our main server was hilarious.  Finally, the price: More than reasonable, in my opinion.  Will definitely come here again, and will order delivery, too! Also hope to check out the upstairs bar area one day.

My friend took me to this place for lunch. As soon as I went to the buffet, I saw cockroach inside one of the dressing. I was shocked and disgusted but didn't want to embarrass my friend so I skipped the dressing and picked up something else and sat down. None of the food was fresh. I grew up eating spicy and foods with flavor from a different culture so I can immediately tell when the test is not normal and if the food is fresh or not. I was 100% sure the food was not fresh. I felt disgusted more and stopped eating. I was scared cockroaches will get in to my purse so I kept moving my purse around far from the wall. I had tried Indian food once at a different location and it was ok. But after my recent experience, I don't think I will ever try Indian food again.

I had my lunch at this place with my friends . Ordered biriyani and the meat wasn’t fresh and lemon juice was just the water no lemon and not sweet too . The guy just gave me plane water and when I complained he just gave me price reduction. I would never recommend this place and my rating is 1 out of 5 .
They serve old food just warm it up for you. Food is not fresh especially meat items. My rate is 1 out of 5. Taste of the food is hilarious. I don’t recommend this restaurant to anyone. 👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻

If you are looking for Indian dishes in DC, this restaurant is a solid pick. Over the many times I have eaten there or ordered take-out, the food has always been fresh and the quality consistent. If you are a fan of sauce, as I am, then this is a place for you, not to mention the wide variety of naans and main dishes to choose from.

If you are looking for Indian dishes in DC, this restaurant is a solid pick. Over the many times I have eaten there or ordered take-out, the food has always been fresh and the quality consistent. If you are a fan of sauce, as I am, then this is a place for you, not to mention the wide variety of naans and main dishes to choose from.
I live close by, so we like to get delivery from here. It is usually very quick, and the food is great! We usually get the chicken tikka masala, the lamb biryani, and garlic naan and all are great!
Not for vegetarians. Probably the worst restaurant I have ever been to. Special talent required to make food this bad.

Got take out from the place - didn't have to wait very long for my food, but the Chicken Tikka masala was just ok (chicken itself was fantastic but the curry was too salty). All in all a good experience - would go to Taj of India for better take out Chicken Tikka Masala.

I have tried Indian food at different places in DC and they were not good. Finally I have found a go to place for Indian food! I specifically liked the chicken curry, broccoli, onion mix and roti. I also ordered their chai (milk tea) and it was absolutely delicious, it has been a while since I have had authentic chai. I definitely will be coming back for lunch or dinner!
I came here to eat with my coworkers for lunch today and loved it! The food is very authentic, I felt like I was eating my friends parents cooking.

I've ordered delivery from flavors of India numerous times but yesterday was the first time that I've dined in--I have to say, the food remained consistently delicious. I always order a mango lassi, beef samosa, garlic naan, and chicken tikka masala--all of course were quite flavorful and not excessively heavy or oily. I've eaten at other Indian restaurants in DC but they were often overpriced and/or not as tasty. I highly recommend eating here if you want high quality Indian food at a reasonable price. In comparison to Indian restaurants in Los Angeles and New York, Flavors of India is still high on my list. It also helps that the staff was very friendly and expedient in their service. I will undoubtedly be ordering from here/dining in again very soon.
The food, service and atmosphere was wonderful. The naan with the cherries,almonds and coconut was the best I ever had. Very reasonable prices!

I really enjoyed my dinner here! We ordered chicken tikka masala and chicken tandoori, and they were both delicious! What really set this apart was the wonderful service - very friendly staff and my water was always full! Finally, they gave us free rice pudding dessert - oh my gosh amazing! I'll definitely be back!'

The food was very good at flavors of India restaurant. It made me feel like I was back in India for sure. Best Naan ever had with the almonds cheeries and coconut. I got the tilapia and gf got the lamb All i can say is delish!

Based on our experience/opinion at dinner today. Visiting DC for a vacation. Unkempt exterior and funky bathroom smell greet you as you approach and enter. The interior looks work but clean. The seat upholstery in our booth was torn and patched up with tape. Not an exciting start to dinner! Service was prompt, ordered Mango lassis and masala tea for drinks. Tea was weak, lassi was a bit too sweet, but tasted fine. Veggie and meat  Thalis (platters with a variety of veggies, Naan and rice for the former; and chicken/lamb/beef and Daal for the latter) were our choice for entrees. Taste was overall good; meat platter needed another veggie though. Dessert was included in the platter price, and turned out to be Rice Kheer (pudding). Latter was a disappointment, as it consisted of condensed milk and rice with no nuts, raisins, saffron, cardamom or other typical condiments/flavorings. Was expecting to have Mango Kulfi, the other dessert advertised, but was informed it was not available! Overall, food (except dessert) was tasty enough but pricey...$120 for four persons!
A clean hole in the wall

Flavors of India is our Indian go-to in DC. I've tried many of the curries and I think they're all quite flavorful. I think the Korma is their best curry dish but the tikka masala is also quite good and not very hot (though I suspect they can make it hot on request). The naan is good too; i think they've recently expanded their naan selection. I saw Peshwari on the menu tonight and I don't recall seeing it before.

Flavors of India is our Indian go-to in DC. I've tried many of the curries and I think they're all quite flavorful. I think the Korma is their best curry dish but the tikka masala is also quite good and not very hot (though I suspect they can make it hot on request). The naan is good too; i think they've recently expanded their naan selection. I saw Peshwari on the menu tonight and I don't recall seeing it before.

Service was very good, and the food is great. I tried the basics - butter chicken, matter panner and samosas. Everything had just the right amount of spice and the portions aren't crazy big as is often the case. Wash everything down with a branded beer and you have the perfect evening.

Very good Indian restaurant. We ordered Eggplant (Bhaingan) masala, Saag/Palak Panneer (Spinach ) and naan. Food was great.  First of all, the parking is tough to find and restaurant folks needs to offer to validate (at least partially) the parking fee for the guests .  Secondly, it was rather impetuous on their part to charge me 18% gratuity. In fact, we appreciated, I wanted to give more tip but this behavior threw me off.
Delicious food ordered a whole spread with my family and love it
Some food was okay, NASTY, NASTY NASTY restroom. Naan was old and sour. Don't eat here unless you have to.

This restaurant does not deserve even half a star. Firstly the food was pathetic. Secondly my brother fell ill because of the stale food served. AND LASTLY THEY ARE FRAUDS. Just because we were Indians they fooled us and charged us 15$ dollars extra apart from the bill and the tax saying that it’s gratuity tax, W thought something was fishy. So we went and asked a few restaurants. What we got to know is that gratuity is what you wish to give them (Tip) but they forcefully charged us and refuse to accept.
Smallest selection for lunch buffet we have ever seen and only chicken. Tandori & naan were decent. Taste were below average in general
Nice food

I really enjoyed my dinner here! We ordered chicken tikka masala and chicken tandoori, and they were both delicious! What really set this apart was the wonderful service - very friendly staff and my water was always full!

Flavors of India is a hidden gem. This was my first visit, and I fully intend to return. It's quaint yet it has a contemporary interior. As soon as you enter you are greeted and warmly treated. I had their tomato soup on a cold night, and it hit the spot. For my main meal, I had the lamb saag and the garlic naan. It was simply delicious.

The tandoori chicken was hands down the best tandoori chicken I've ever had. It was well seasoned and very tender. Most Indian places I've been to tend to overcook the chicken and dry it out. Not so here! The naan bread was perfectly cooked and very fresh but nothing too special. We regrettably didn't try any flavored naan.
I live close by, so we like to get delivery from here. It is usually very quick, and the food is great! We usually get the chicken tikka masala, the lamb biryani, and garlic naan and all are great!
Everything we had was delicious; the service was prompt, courteous, and friendly.  The price for our meal was also very reasonable.

Excellent service and great food. We saw a show at the Kennedy Center and walked right here. We were pleasantly surprised with free dessert. One of the best places for Indian I've been in DC. Will certainly be back. Great outdoor seating area, ultra affordable prices and there's a bar upstairs!
Great food.  Try their fried Spinach Salad!  Their Lamb Saag is great.  Overall the food and service is great.
Absolutely delicious! The lunch buffet is always fresh. The dishes are reasonably priced.  The staff was very accommodating and this is quickly become one of my favorite restaurants in DC!

The taste of chicken tikka masala and papadam was very nice.  The chicken was moist and the sauce wasn't too sweet.  The garlic bread was really good, though I've had some better. But overall, the restaurant is really good.
The best way I could describe it would be fast food. Cheaper but artificial.
Our waiter was presumptuous😯
Worst restaurant. Too much dirty and food is tasteless
Tried their lamb and chicken biryani, it was excellent!

Online ordering is extremely painful and inflexible. Had an Horrible experience and lost money. Paid but no food. Placed the order online, received no notification about the order, and there was no one when i went to pick up the order.   Online ordering through qMenu is painful. They denied to refund my money.

The food was delicious! We had the chana saag and the vegetable korma with garlic naan. The main dishes were tasty, though the naan just ok--not as fluffy as some. The staff was very attentive (almost overattentive) and made sure our glasses were always full of water.  All in all a good experience with great cuisine and service.

Great food and great service in a perfect location - will comeback for Chicken Dhaniya & Chicken Tikka Salad. My friend loved the mixed grill and naan. Awesome mango kulfi. No need to go walk extra blocks.
Good food Hot Tasty Portion sizes just right, I had leftovers. Fast service Very clean restaurant Small, intimate and Cozy! I would return! Support local businesses
It is my favorite Indian place by far. The staff is always friendly and nice and the food always on time. It never gets old. A little gem hidden in a perfect location.
Good stuff. I got the Tandoori chicken, which was nice and spicy, with some sauteed veggies that were nice and tender. Wait staff was very attentive, refilling water glasses frequently.

The food was pretty tasty and surprisingly spicy. We ordered most dished as "medium" spice.  I know Indian food level of spice can be a bit more intense than what salsa levels might be.  So I wasn't too surprised when those foods were spicy, compared to a hot level salsa at the store.  Pretty light, not greasy, well flavored.  Will definitely order from here again.

Randomly walked in there for lunch, and the food was great! The staff is very attentive and very polite. The paneer tikka was delish! I really enjoyed the lamb vindaloo too. It's def a good choice if you like spicy food. When we left, we were given menus to bring to friends.

First off with the serving plate sizes, there $ value doesn't match. It's even less than a small plate. We ordered a gravy with naan, we had to throw out the meat to find the gravy sticking barely to the bottom of the tray. The balance between the meat and gravy doesn't match, forget the taste please get the appropriately potions to serve. Biryani sucks to the core ,again the balance between the rice and meat is a perfect mismatch.

Got food poisoning from either the "eggplant," the salmon, or one of the dairy desserts.  Spent the next 24hrs alternating between diarrhea and vomiting.  Great place to visit for unintentional weight loss.
I had to spend the whole day in DC, so I'd say to eat here! The buffet was very good!

We ordered a takeout of chicken Tikka Masala and paneer Tikka Masala from flavors on our visit to Washington. The food was really bad with the kulchas hard and the aloo paratha lacked taste. Not worth the price at all. Really bad food.

Quaint little restaurant with great food and excellent customer service. You can really tell that they want you to enjoy their food and your experience. Our waiter asked all our names and introduced himself. The food was flavorful, I ordered a chicken dish. I would definitely return if I were to visit DC again

Great food, very good service, nice climate. Especially goot lamb curry and butter masala. I'm not a big fan of putting ice cubes into mango lassi, but the drink itself was great. Go there when you like Indian cuisine!
Excellent taste and price is also reasonable.
Did a take out from here. Very bad food. Panner makhni gravy was like thin watery soup! Paneer was hard and bad. Terrible experience.
Worst restroom and food was really bad....seriously never opt and get pulled by fake ratings......
I tried the Veg Biryani and Cardamom Tea. The Biryani was prepared well but was not flavorful as you would expect. The tea was disappointing.

I did take out, and was happy with the food. The price was ok and the quality was there. The sides were unique, I feel rather authentic.  Take out packaging was good, not spilling all over as I biked home.
Awesome food and great service. Dishes felt very authentic Chicken vindaloo is fiery and delicious.
Service was very good, and the food is great. I tried the basics - butter chicken, matter panner. Everything had just the right amount of spice and the portions aren't crazy big as is often the case.

I love almost all the dishes I've tried here. The spices and the flavors are rightly balanced to remind one of what a good made Indian meal must be like. I love the feel of the place, the hindi tunes that float around and the hospitality of the staffs! Very strongly recommend this place. My personal favorites are spinach chat, chicken korma, madras chicken and paneer saag !

I love Indian food, so we had to check out the new sit-down place in DC.  I was pleased to see a vegetarian thali on the menu.  I am all about getting little tastes of a lot of different things.  As per the menu, it has Aloo Gobi Masala (potato and cauliflower curry), Saag Paneer (spinach and homemade cheese curry), Bengan Bhartha (eggplant), and lentils.  It comes with rice, naan, raita and dessert.  The food was all quite tasty.
Food was great. Best Indian food I have had in years. Service was excellent! I will be coming back! The chicken saag was very good!
Real taste of Indian food
Real taste of Indian food.
I ordered for a plate of chana masala and must say that I have become a fan of this place ever since.
They have an awesome collection of seafood items. Would love to place this place more to try out all of these.
Every time I wish to try out some Indian variants, this is the one place I always trust.
This is my go-to restaurant whenever I seek Indian food choices like Paneer kadai. They are amazing with Indian food items.
Had a plate full of chicken Vindaloo and it was delicious. Even better was the surrounding with rich great cultural ambiance.
The staff was extremely nice and food quality was awesome. I ordered the Chicken chana dal and it was nothing less than heaven.
Good  very nice

As per the menu, it has Aloo Gobi Masala (potato and cauliflower curry), Saag Paneer (spinach and homemade cheese curry), Bengan Bhartha (eggplant), and lentils.  It comes with rice, naan, raita and dessert.  The food was all quite tasty, though not the best Indian food ever. I didn't care for the eggplant too much, and unfortunately I am writing this several weeks after the fact, but I think that I got something other than aloo gobi that was equally underwhelming.
Food was okay. Chicken Tikka Masala was a unique receipe, not my favorite.

It tasted much sweeter than I recall it tasting other times that I'd had it, it kind of tasted like it had cinnamon in it and personally I am not a fan of cinnamon in anything other than dessert. The manager and the staff pretty much insisted on making me something else, and kept saying how they just really wanted us to be happy with our experience there. Far surpassing expectations. All in all the food was amazing and the service, even better! They were so kind and attentive which was very refreshing. I would definitely go back.

Overlooked chicken tikka in a salad made chewing a challenge. And, bottled Italian dressing hardly helped this salad.
Average

Small selection of the staple foods on the buffet, but when I say small selection I mean small. Maybe 8 pans of food were set out, one of which was rice. The food was tasty, and you could still order from the full menu during the lunch hours of you wanted to.
Solid choice for lunch buffet if a bit pricey. It's down in the basement though.

Flavors of India was a great place to go after a long day of traveling. The staff was very generous when it came to the portions of each plate ordered. We had paneer tikka masala, the malai kofta as well as few other dishes. The different types of chutney given to start off your night was definitely a recipe we wanted to get our hands on, haha! Every single one of the employees made sure we were satisfied with our food which was awesome! Very affordable. Definitely recommended!

This place wasn't too bad. The spicy wasn't all that spicy but the Naan was great. Was it the best a Indian food? No but it got the job done. A bit dark in there and empty. Take from that what you will.
Good, spicy food in an otherwise bland culinary landscape of DC
It is good restaurant where we can have all flavours of India

This was the worst indian food I've ever had. I ordered using the "Caviar" delivery service. The chicken tikka masala and lamb curry, had no flavor, no spice, and had a curdled consistency. The meat had a strange and disconcerting texture as well. I would recommend that you do not eat from this restaurant.

Flavors of India ranks three and a half to four stars for me.  I will admit that we have only done takeout, and that we are slightly biased by our extreme love for Karavalli in Latham, but Flavors of India offers solid Indian food.  My dining partner and I order from here fairly often. I always have ordered chicken tikka masala and chicken korma.  I know it's not the most exciting, but those are among our favorites.  I love that I am always asked about heat level.  Although tikka masala generally comes as a mild dish automatically at most places I have ordered it, I am always asked my preferred spice level here. I have asked for medium and spicy, and I now ask for somewhere on between medium and spicy!  I think the kick of heat adds a really nice flavor to the creaminess of the masala. My dining partner is spice-shy, so he gets his korma mild, but really enjoys the subtle flavors and non-heat spices it offers.  The portions are not huge, but usually plenty enough that I get a dinner out of it and a lunch the next day.  My only drawback for Flavors of India thus far is that I am not a big fan of their naan.  We always get the plain, and it has always come across to be a little dry and crumbly to me.  Perhaps it'll be better when we finally dine-in.  The prices are a hair high, but to me, the quality is worth it.  And speaking of dining in, the restaurant really is lovely.  I'll be coming back here for something other than take out -- and maybe something other than chicken tikka masala soon!
Okay to satisfy hunger, not that Authentic. Ordered Aloo saag and it was okay which came with complimentary rice. Also cheese naan was not so cheesy.

It was two of us that had gone to this restaurant around 10:30 at night, due to coming straight from a cruise ride.  Luckily, because the reservation was made well in advance, they let us in.  Still, I was walking on eggshells because I was hoping they don't rush us or make the food mediocre.  Although the person we had told us they needed our order quickly, we were pleased with the general treatment.  We were well attended to, our food was made quickly and the naan bread was seemingly fresh.  I actually liked the mattar paneer with the rice, the naan, and samosas.  Although, the meat samosa took my surprise at the high level of meatiness, it still tastes delicious with the chutney.  Plus, the manager was friendly with us. Truthfully, everything was better than I expected for the time that we showed up.  Thank you, Taste of India!

Lapin and I came here for dinner while visiting DC.  We both were craving Indian food and this was within walking distance.  We were seated quickly as the restaurant was only 30% full. The service was mediocre. They never came by to ask about how the meal was. When I asked them what was an entree was made with, the waiter gave me a snark response.  They spilled water all over the table a couple of times and pretty much ignored us for a good portion of the time. They also tried charging us 25% tip, perhaps thinking we were tourists (which we were but I been to DC before).  We ordered the Vegetable platter - a combo of vegetable samosa, veggie Pakora, chicken tikka and beef sheek kabab to share. I am not sure how chicken and beef is considered a vegetable platter but whatever. It came with one piece of each and it was pretty tasty. I ordered the chicken curry ($12) but the waiter said their more expensive Chicken Vindaloo ($13) was a better option. Thanks for the recommendation, but I didn't really like being asked multiple times if I was sure about my order. The chicken curry came with basmati rice and it was decent.  Lapin ordered the Meat Thali ($20) - an assortment of chicken makhani, lamb palak, beef curry, and lentils served with Basmati rice, naan, and riata. Lapin liked everything except the lamb palak because it had too much spinach. We also ordered a mango kulfi which was very small and hard to break apart. We warmed the spoons with the candle on the table to help break the dessert apart but it was still very hard to eat.  The food is decent but the service is lacking.

They charged us gratuity for a table of 4 adults and 1 child! The reasoning was because we were going to use a "Groupon"? Really??? May be they reconsider of advertising on Groupon - it's a joke. The food certainly gets 3+ stars, but they failed in "Customer Service" - wouldn't be surprised if they even know what that means!!!

The worst experience ever. It was the two of us, my wife and I. Ordered a bunch of things.. They messed up our order. The food was horrible and not even close to authentic. The manager was super rude as if he didn't wanna be there. Lastly, they added gratuity in the bill.. It wasn't even a group.. Just the two of us. Horrible horrible place. Their naans were ridiculously made with no butter or any grease. Yuck!
NOT RECOMMENDED!! We hated it. half cooked TASTELESS FOOD, high priced menu, tiny quantity, understaffed and took 47 minuted to bring appetizers and another 55 minutes for the main course.
Ok. So food was ok, typical home made food test, not feel like real restaurant food.. And services was ok too.
Very good! They were very busy at 8:30 on a Tuesday night. Excellent service. We had the chicken vindaloo and the chicken curry with some naan bread. On vacation and this was a great find!

I can not speak for the restaurant itself as I have not been there, I ordered delivery from here via Try Caviar. We've eaten at several other Indian restaurants in DC. This one was really our least favorite. The food was not bad, but just not that good compared to the others. The Pashwari Naan stuffed with  cherry, coconut, almonds and raisins was interesting, but otherwise nothing special.

I tried putting 0 stars. It was really strange. It's January 14, 2015. It's cold as hell outside. When I went inside, it felt just as cold. I expressed my discomfort to the waiter but did not receive an apology or an explanation. I thought it was just me, but then I started seeing their staff walking around wearing sweaters, winter hats, and scarves.  I left a tip for the waiter and then he gave me back my receipt saying "Tip is not included," suggesting he wanted additional tip. That was just confusing for me...  Lastly, the food was subpar. Definitely was not worth the trip heading there. We went for their lunchtime buffet. Selection was very minimal and it lacked taste in comparison to all the other Indian restaurants that I've eaten at.

Food was good. Ridiculously highly priced for a little plate of items. They also cheated us on food order. Every chicken tikka masala or paneer makhkhan or alu gobi should come with a side. They did not gave us anything. Terrible customer service. I saw zero level of professionalism among the staff. Very rude. Also, they treated us differently than other customers.
Really tasty meal and friendly staff. Didn't expect much, but was pleasantly surprised.
Really good food - though a few times the food was stale and the meat of low quality.

Open for about a year, when these guys plot off from Taj of India I was very hopeful. The food is always good, the service is friendly, and I am a regular. For Indian food that isn't trying to be fine dining the flavors are subtle and they have some dishes not available elsewhere. I hope they do well enough to be able to upgrade the restaurant because a makeover is badly needed.
Excellent restaurant,  food was great, service is amazing. Highly recommended.

THIS PLACE IS HORRIBLE! STAY AWAY!  FIrst of all the amount of food that you get for the amount of money that you spend is completely disproportionate.  I ordered 45 dollars worth of food and got enough food to only feed two people.  The portions are way too small.  Now this would be fine if the food was delicious right?  Unfortunately this is not the case.  The curry was made with SPOILED MILK and everything was disgusting.  I had to throw the entire order out after being overwhelmed by the aroma of spoiled milk.  If I had eaten it I'm sure I would be admitted in a hospital ER the next day for food poisoning.  Do yourself a favor and DO NOT ORDER FROM THIS PLACE.  There was one positive however, the guy who delivered our food was really nice.. although he was lost for about 5 minutes before he realized he was standing right in front of our door.
